The Turkish top-flight outfit has snapped up the former Flamingoes midfielder following a successful trial from Confluence Queens. READ ALSO  Wike vows to make Real Madrid Academy world-class institution Turkish Kadınlar Ligi side Adana Idmanyurduspor have completed the signing of Nigeria midfielder Ramat Abdulkareem on a one-year deal with a 12-month extension option. Abdulkareem wrapped up her first move to Europe from Nigeria Women’s Premier League top-flight side Confluence Queens before the transfer window was closed following a successful trial. The 20-year-old, who previously starred for Nasarawa Amazons, Abia Angels and Adamawa Queens in Nigeria, played a part in the Lokoja outfit’s qualification to the Super Four event this season.